The Herald LONDON. — Liverpool’s perfect start to the English Premier League football season is under threat from an in-form Leicester led by a manager with a point to prove at Anfield in Brendan Rodgers. English Premiership Fixtures (all 4pm unless otherwise stated) Today: Brighton v Tottenham (1:30pm); Burnley v Everton; Liverpool v Leicester City; Norwich v Aston Villa; Watford v Sheffield United; West Ham v Crystal Palace (6:30pm). Tomorrow: Southampton v Chelsea; Arsenal v Bournemouth; Manchester City v Wolves (all 3pm); Newcastle v Manchester United (5:30pm). — AFP.